Operation Sticker Shock
-----------------------------41433982563113152741235501582
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="activityDate"

2024-07-19
-----------------------------41433982563113152741235501582
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="hours"

5
-----------------------------41433982563113152741235501582
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

I got the opportunity to partner with Olathe CTC (Communities that Care) and the Olathe Police Department to hang bottle hangers that tell people not to sell alcohol to minors. We went to around 20 stores and distributed these bottle hangers on necks of vodka, whiskey, fireballs, and other colorful products that would appeal to minors attempting to buy alcohol. The store-owners were generally happy with what we were doing, and in previous years, Olathe CTC had gone to most of the stores that we also went to. This means that the store-owners were happy with the services we were doing for the community. This project seems to be somewhat successful as Johnson County has seen a decline in underage alcohol use when they started using this program. I also think it was a success because us students got free pizza and got to ride in the "cage" of police vehicles.
